# PowerShell Script Standards

Apply these conventions when generating or modifying PowerShell scripts. See `scripts.instructions.md` for cross-platform conventions.

## Script header

```powershell
[CmdletBinding()]
param(
    [switch]$VerboseOutput,
    [switch]$SkipInstall,
    [string]$Config = "",
    [switch]$Help
)

if ($Help) {
    Write-Host "Script Name" -ForegroundColor Blue
    Write-Host ""
    Write-Host "USAGE:" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "  .\scripts\script-name.ps1 [options]"
    Write-Host ""
    Write-Host "OPTIONS:" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "  -VerboseOutput    Enable verbose output"
    Write-Host "  -SkipInstall      Skip tool installation/updates"
    Write-Host "  -Config <path>    Custom config file path"
    Write-Host "  -Help             Show this help"
    exit 0
}

$ErrorActionPreference = "Stop"
```

## Naming conventions

- Variables: `PascalCase` — `$ProjectRoot`, `$ConfigPath`
- Switch params: `PascalCase` — `-SkipInstall`, `-VerboseOutput`
- Use `-VerboseOutput` not `-Verbose` to avoid conflicts with the built-in `$VerbosePreference`

## Path construction

```powershell
$ScriptDir   = Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path
$ProjectRoot = Split-Path -Parent $ScriptDir

$BackendDir  = Join-Path $ProjectRoot "backend"
$ConfigPath  = Join-Path $ProjectRoot ".golangci.yml"
```

## Output functions

```powershell
function Write-Status  { param([string]$Message) Write-Host "[INFO] $Message"    -ForegroundColor Cyan }
function Write-Success { param([string]$Message) Write-Host "[SUCCESS] $Message" -ForegroundColor Green }
function Write-Warn    { param([string]$Message) Write-Host "[WARNING] $Message" -ForegroundColor Yellow }
function Write-Fail    { param([string]$Message) Write-Host "[ERROR] $Message"   -ForegroundColor Red }
```

## Exit code checking

```powershell
go build ./...
if ($LASTEXITCODE -ne 0) {
    Write-Fail "Go build failed"
    exit 1
}
Write-Success "Build succeeded"
```

## Error handling

```powershell
try {
    Set-Location $BackendDir
    # operations
} catch {
    Write-Fail "Operation failed: $($_.Exception.Message)"
    exit 1
} finally {
    Set-Location $OriginalLocation
}
```

## Calling component scripts

```powershell
$componentScript = Join-Path $ScriptDir "backend\backend_test.ps1"
$args = @()
if ($VerboseOutput) { $args += "-VerboseOutput" }
if ($SkipInstall)   { $args += "-SkipInstall" }
& $componentScript @args
if ($LASTEXITCODE -ne 0) { exit $LASTEXITCODE }
```
